This paper is about improving the efficiency of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) using tensor decompositions. The primary focus is on computer vision applications, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a new algorithm for computing the low-rank tensor decomposition, which involves optimization techniques that are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the performance of various CNN architectures, which suggests that it may be relevant to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of mathematical techniques for reducing the redundancy in CNNs, which suggests that it may be relevant to the data structures (cs.DS) sub-category.
